snippet.textDisplay: The guy in the analysis room seems not to respect Arteta. I think that should fire all the guys in the analysis room since they are not helpful. All the Arsenal players in a few last games do not know about what is the SWOT of their competitor team. Arteta also should change the training way, all the arsenal players are trained to pass the ball to their teammate as soon as possible, they don't know how to hold the ball and wait for their teammate to move to an advantageous position to pass the ball. The consequence of this action is Arsenal always has more than their competitor about the number of passes the ball but the created chance is less than their competitor. Auba is a good striker, his strength is the speed why we don't make him play like Vardy, use more the long pass. Pepe is great in one to one, he also able to plays at Auba's position. Lacazette is a perfect striker, he able to play any position, he is good at in narrow. If an Arsenal player wants to get a score, they just need to run around Lacazette and wait for him to pass the ball. Arsenal is lacking the muscle in the middle field like Viera and the defensive position like SolCampel I don't know why we don't recruit players for these positions. I am just a student in the business analysis major and I can realize Arsenal's problems. I don't know why Arsenal does not realize the problems or they realize them but they choose to ignore it.
